, interpersonal conflicts, personal safety, transition issues, and physical and mental health concerns.       Student Assistance Request      Student Assistance           Academic Concerns  Assistance for students navigating academic challenges             Health & Personal Concerns  Support for students experiencing significant medical, mental health, safety or financial challenges             Campus Life Issues  Assistance for students on everything from planning a protest to giving personal feedback on staff interactions          Student Assistance           Faculty and Staff Resources  Consultation and resources to assist faculty and staff working with students in distress             U & I Care  UIC’s network of care for students              Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 3030 SSB Chicago, IL 60607  Phone: (312) 996-4857  dos@uic.edu        Social Media Accounts             UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Saf